“Nothing stops the man who desires to achieve. Every obstacles is simply a course to develop his achievement muscle. It's a strengthening of his powers of accomplishment.”  – Eric Butterworth, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
“I thank God for my handicaps, for through them, I have found myself, my work and my God.”  – Helen Keller, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
“As a rule adversity reveals genius and prosperity hides it.”  – Horace, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
“What does not kill me makes me stronger.”  – Johann Wolfgang von Goethe, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
“Out of suffering comes the serious mind; out of salvation, the grateful heart; out of endurance, fortitude; out of deliverance faith.”  – John Ruskin, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
“Life is a grindstone. But whether it grinds us down or polishes us up depends on us.”  – L. Thomas Holdcroft, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
“Adversity is the midwife of genius.”  – Napoleon Bonaparte, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
“The darkest hour is just before the dawn.”  – Proverb, The Collected Works of Abraham Lincoln
